        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Q: Do I need a second phone to use Unitel Voice?",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "A: Nope. That's the whole point. Unitel Voice forwards calls to your existing cell phone or landline. You answer business calls on the same device you already carry. Your callers hear your professional greeting and IVR — they never know you're picking up from your couch.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Q: Can I port my existing business number to Unitel Voice?",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "A: Yes. If you already have a business number you want to keep, Unitel Voice supports number porting. You can transfer it into their system and get all the virtual phone features without losing your established number.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Q: How many extensions can I create?",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "A: The number of extensions depends on your plan, but even the basic plans give you enough for a small team or multiple department routing. Each extension can ring to a different phone number, making it flexible for distributed teams.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Q: Is there a contract or long-term commitment?",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "A: Unitel Voice offers plans without long-term contracts. You can pay monthly and cancel anytime. This is a huge advantage over traditional business phone providers that lock you into 12- or 24-month agreements.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Q: Can I use Unitel Voice for outbound calls too?",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "A: Absolutely. When you make calls through the Unitel Voice system, your business number shows up on the recipient's caller ID. This keeps your personal number private while maintaining a consistent professional identity.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Q: What happens to calls after business hours?",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "A: You configure this yourself. After hours, calls can go to a custom voicemail greeting, ring to a different number (like an answering service), or simply inform callers of your business hours. You're in full control of the caller experience around the clock.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
